      <TR>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top' nowrap><b><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>exnec</font></b></td>
        <TD bgcolor='dimgray' valign='top'><font color='white' face='Verdana, Arial, Helvetica' size='2'>Excellent overview of the Necro class, Daedrea.  Right on the mark and well written.</P><P>I retired from EQ as a 53 necro, roughly 10 months ago.  I wasn't a hard core player, but I had been around for a while, long enough to see round after round of nerfs to the class, and while I wasn't as high level as some of you, 53 was enough to get frustrated at many things.</P><P>I spent a fair bit of time in the class balance threads on the station boards trying to suggest reasonable fixes - things that would _not_ improve our solo power, but would instead improve our ability to fit into the end game.  Of course, it was all for naught.  I eventually quite EQ entirely.  The only real way to send a message, IMHO, is to stop paying them.</P><P>My basic problems with the class line up fairly well with yours.  They were something like this:</P><P>(A) Post-50 pets needed a significant HP boost and a slight damage boost.  The 49 pet beating the crap out of a 56 pet is just crazy.  Higher pets could use some resists too, to live for more than a round or two with AEs.</P><P>(B) Necro stackability - wizard and warrior damage stacks 100% with other wizards and warriors - why can't our damage do the same?  Even our IB DD was made unstackable.</P><P>(C) Inability to land spells on boss mobs.  Maybe this is better now?</P><P>(D) Our contribution goes down as fights get shorter.  In 3-5 group situations, the yard trash dies in 15 seconds or less much of the time.  What good is a 2 minute DOT in a 15 second fight?  Many times creatures would die about at the end of my _cast time_ for DOTs, so of course I didn't DOT in fight likely to end fast.  But we're build around DOTs!  Even exp groups tend to rip through mobs in 30 sec or less, if they know what they're doing.</P><P>A few ideas I had at the time:</P><P>(1) Make our DOT duration vary inversely with the size of the group.  Take a 2 min dot.  Maybe it would run in 2 minutes solo, 1 minute in a 3 man group, and 30 seconds in a 6 man group.  I just made those numbers up, but it could be tuned as appropriate.  It wouldn't effect our solo power one bit, but would make us more group friendly.  No more finishing the cast on a DOT, only to have the creature die in the next tick or two.  Aggro would have to be handled appropriately.</P><P>(2) There appear to be game engine issues with making dots stackable, but there is an easy alternative.  The first necro to land a particular DOT on a creature sets the DOT timer going.  The 2nd, 3rd, etc to land the _same_ dot don't start new timers, they just increment a DOT count.  Each tick, the creaure takes damage equal to the DOT damage per tick times the count.  This "fakes" a limited form of stackability.  When you only have 1 or 2 DOTs that can land on a creature, this would let the 2nd and 3rd necros contribute damage (we are, after all, damage dealers!)  Even when many dots will land, often only one or two are practical due to the fight not lasting long enough for the long ones, and only a few of our dots run through in under a minute.</P><P>(3) Give the poor 50+ jobobers some more HP.  No way should they go _backwards_ and lose fights to the 49 pet!  That's just crazy.</P><P>(4) An essence emerald for a high level lifetap?  Who was the brainiac who came up with that one?  Essence emeralds would be an OK thing if they were _not used up_!</P><P>If they would have just made us more stackable, able to cast on boss creatures, and given us something real to look forward to post-50, I'd still be playing the game.  But they didn't, and I'm not.  I won't be back, but I do still have a fondness for the necro class.  It was lots of fun while it lasted.</P><P>Best of luck to all of you who still play.  Me, I'm waiting for the Next Great MMPORG.</P><P></P><P> </font></td>
      </tr>
      <TR>
